  "body": " Classifying a Number as Odd, Even, Prime or Composite   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Classifying a given number as odd, even, prime or composite    <p>During a math lesson, Grade 10 students were asked to classify the number <strong>{@seven_digit@}<\/strong> as even, odd, prime or composite.<\/p> <p>Which of the following are true about this number? Select all that apply:<b> [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]] <\/p>    <p>Worked Solution<\/p> <p>Given the number: {@seven_digit@}:<\/p> <p>Test if it is Even or Odd :<\/p> <p>Check the last digit<\/p> <p>{@if is_even then sconcat(\"Since the last digit is (\", mod(seven_digit, 10), \") it is even.\") else sconcat(\"Since the last digit is (\", mod(seven_digit, 10), \") it is odd.\") @}<\/p> <p>Check if it is Prime or Composite:<\/p> <p>{@if seven_digit = 1 then \"1 is a special number: neither prime nor composite.\" else if is_prime_num then sconcat(\"After testing divisibility up to \", floor(sqrt(seven_digit)), \", no divisors found except 1 and itself. Therefore, it is prime.\") else block([factor: composite_factor], sconcat(seven_digit, \" ÷ \", factor, \" = \", seven_digit\/factor, \"<br>Since it has a divisor other than 1 and itself, it is composite.\") ) @}<\/p> <p>Therefore, {@seven_digit@} is {@t_ans1@} <\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Generate 5-digit random number *\/ seven_digit: rand(90000) + 10000; \/* Even\/Odd *\/ is_even: mod(seven_digit,2)=0; \/* Prime check *\/ is_prime(n) := if n<2 then false else if n=2 then true else if mod(n,2)=0 then false else block([limit:floor(sqrt(n)),i:3,result:true], while i<=limit and result do ( if mod(n,i)=0 then result:false, i:i+2 ), result ); is_prime_num: is_prime(seven_digit); \/* Labels *\/ option_labels: [\"it is even\",\"it is odd\",\"it is prime\",\"it is composite\"]; option_flags: [is_even, not is_even, is_prime_num, (not is_prime_num and seven_digit>1)]; \/* Teacher answer (correct labels) *\/ t_ans1: []; for i:1 thru length(option_labels) do ( if option_flags[i] then t_ans1: append(t_ans1,[option_labels[i]]) ); perm: random_permutation(makelist(i,i,1,length(option_labels))); ta: makelist([ option_labels[perm[i]], option_labels[perm[i]] ], i, 1, length(option_labels)); \/* Composite factor for feedback *\/ composite_factor: if not is_prime_num and seven_digit>1 then block([f:0], if mod(seven_digit,2)=0 then f:2 else if mod(seven_digit,3)=0 then f:3 else for k:5 step 2 while k*k<=seven_digit and f=0 do ( if mod(seven_digit,k)=0 then f:k ), f ) else 0; \/* Build correct answer display string *\/ correct_answers_str: sconcat(\"<p>\", stringjoin(correct_answers, \"<br>\"), \"<\/p>\");       <p> {@seven_digit@}<\/p>      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  checkbox  ta  15  1  0   0    1  0  0  0  0  nonotanswered    prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0   AlgEquiv  ans1  t_ans1   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F          "
