  "body": " Classifying Given Numbers as Irrational   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Classifying given numbers as irrational    <p>Which of the following numbers are irrational? Select all that apply.<\/p> <p>[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <p>Worked Solution<\/p> <p>An irrational number cannot be expressed as a fraction \\( \\frac{p}{q} \\) where \\( p \\) and \\( q \\) are integers.<\/p> <p>Note that:<\/p> <ul> <li>\\( \\sqrt{n} \\) is irrational when \\( n \\) is not a perfect square<\/li> <li>\\( \\pi \\) and \\( e \\) are irrational<\/li> <li>Decimals that neither terminate nor repeat are irrational<\/li> <\/ul> <p>Therefore, irrational numbers in this list are: \\({@correct_answers[1][3]@},{@correct_answers[2][3]@},{@correct_answers[3][3]@}\\)<\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Pool of irrational expressions (true) *\/ irrationals_all: [ pi, sqrt(2), sqrt(3), sqrt(5), 2*sqrt(2), pi - 3, sqrt(8), 0.121221222, 3*sqrt(7), sqrt(10), e, sqrt(11), pi\/2, sqrt(13), sqrt(17), sqrt(19), sqrt(23), sqrt(29) ]; \/* Pool of rational expressions (false) *\/ rationals_all: [ 5, -4, 7\/3, 0.25, 3\/10, sqrt(25), sqrt(49), 12\/5, 0.12121212, -9, 4\/7, 0, -13, 1.5, 2\/3, sqrt(36), sqrt(100), 0.33333333, -2.5, 0.75, sqrt(64), 0.6 ]; \/* Select correct answers (irrational numbers) *\/ num_correct: 3; correct_answers: rand_selection([ [1, true, irrationals_all[1]], [2, true, irrationals_all[2]], [3, true, irrationals_all[3]], [4, true, irrationals_all[4]], [5, true, irrationals_all[5]], [6, true, irrationals_all[6]], [7, true, irrationals_all[7]], [8, true, irrationals_all[8]], [9, true, irrationals_all[9]], [10, true, irrationals_all[10]] ], num_correct); \/* Select incorrect answers (rational numbers) *\/ num_incorrect: 3; incorrect_answers: rand_selection([ [11, false, rationals_all[1]], [12, false, rationals_all[2]], [13, false, rationals_all[3]], [14, false, rationals_all[4]], [15, false, rationals_all[5]], [16, false, rationals_all[6]], [17, false, rationals_all[7]], [18, false, rationals_all[8]], [19, false, rationals_all[9]], [20, false, rationals_all[10]] ], num_incorrect); \/* Combine and randomize *\/ ta: random_permutation(append(correct_answers, incorrect_answers)); ta_largest: length(ta);       <p>{@irrationals_all@}<\/p> <p>{@rationals_all@}<\/p>      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  checkbox  ta  15  1  0   0    1  0  0  0  0  nonotanswered    prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for correct classification of rational and irrational numbers  AlgEquiv  ans1  mcq_correct(ta)   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F   <p> You have to select a list of irrational numbers only. Kindly check the worked solution to see how classify to numbers.<\/p>     1692903785     "
