  "body": " Classifying Rational Numbers from a List   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Classifying rational numbers given a list of real numbers    <p>Grade 10 maths teacher has a magical number sorter that only accepts rational numbers. The following numbers are ready to be sorted. Which of them will be accepted?<br> Select all rational numbers.<\/p> <\/p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <h3>Worked Solution<\/h3> <p>A rational number is any number that can be expressed as a fraction \\( \\frac{p}{q} \\) where \\( p \\) and \\( q \\) are integers and \\( q \\neq 0 \\).<\/p> <p>The decimal representation of a rational number either terminates (stops at some point) or repeats (continues but has a repeating pattern).<\/p> <p>The square root of a perfect square is a rational number.<\/p> <p>Therefore, from the given numbers, the list of rational numbers are: ({@correct_answers[1][3]@},{@correct_answers[2][3]@},{@correct_answers[3][3]@})<\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Pool of rational expressions (true) *\/ rationals_all: [ 5, -4, 7\/3, 0.25, 3\/10, sqrt(25), sqrt(49), 12\/5, 0.12121212, -9, 4\/7, 0, -13, 1.5, 2\/3, sqrt(36), sqrt(100), 0.33333333 ]; \/* Pool of irrational expressions (false) *\/ irrationals_all: [ pi, sqrt(2), sqrt(3), sqrt(5), 2*sqrt(2), pi - 3, sqrt(8), 0.121221222, 3*sqrt(7), sqrt(10), e, sqrt(11), pi\/2, sqrt(13) ]; \/* Select correct answers (rational numbers) *\/ num_correct: 3; correct_answers: rand_selection([ [1, true, rationals_all[1]], [2, true, rationals_all[2]], [3, true, rationals_all[3]], [4, true, rationals_all[4]], [5, true, rationals_all[5]], [6, true, rationals_all[6]], [7, true, rationals_all[7]], [8, true, rationals_all[8]], [9, true, rationals_all[9]], [10, true, rationals_all[10]] ], num_correct); \/* Select incorrect answers (irrational numbers) *\/ num_incorrect: 3; incorrect_answers: rand_selection([ [11, false, irrationals_all[1]], [12, false, irrationals_all[2]], [13, false, irrationals_all[3]], [14, false, irrationals_all[4]], [15, false, irrationals_all[5]], [16, false, irrationals_all[6]], [17, false, irrationals_all[7]], [18, false, irrationals_all[8]], [19, false, irrationals_all[9]], [20, false, irrationals_all[10]] ], num_incorrect); \/* Combine and randomize *\/ ta: random_permutation(append(correct_answers, incorrect_answers)); ta_largest: length(ta);       <p>{@rationals_all@}<\/p> <p>{@irrationals_all@}<\/p>      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  checkbox  ta  15  1  0   0    1  0  0  0  0  nonotanswered    prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct selection of rational numbers  AlgEquiv  ans1  mcq_correct(ta)   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F   <p> You have failed to select the correct list of rational numbers. Kindly check on the worked solution below<\/p>     1842945592     "
