  "body": " Expressing Cube Power Results in Index Form   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Expressing cube power results in index form    <p>A school has a computer storage server that saves student work in blocks. Each block holds repeated copies of the same unit file. One unit file has a size of \\({@base@}\\) MB. After processing, the total saved size is \\({@number@}\\) MB.<\/p> <p>Write \\({@number@}\\) in index form using base \\({@base@}\\).<\/p> <p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <h3>Worked Solution<\/h3> <p>The total saved size is \\({@number@}\\) MB.<\/p> <p>We check how many times \\({@base@}\\) appears as a repeated factor:<\/p> <p>\\({@number@} = {@base@} \\times {@base@} \\times \\dots \\times {@base@}\\) (repeated {@exp@} times)<\/p> <p>Thus, the index form is:<\/p> <p>\\[ {@base@}^{@exp@}. \\]<\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Random base from common perfect powers *\/ base: rand([2,3,5,7]); \/* Random exponent (bigger than Question 1) *\/ exp: rand([3,4,5]); \/* Actual number *\/ number: base^exp; \/* Common mistakes *\/ m1: base * exp; \/* multiplication instead of exponent *\/ m2: exp ^ base; \/* reversed exponent *\/ m3: base + exp; \/* addition *\/       <p>Base: {@base@}<\/p> <p>Exponent: {@exp@}<\/p> <p>Number: {@number@}<\/p>    <p id=\"author\">Michael Onyimbo<\/p> <p id=\"concept\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"description\"> The question requires the learner to rewrite a large number in index form within a real-life context by recognising how many times a given base is multiplied to produce the total value.<\/p>   1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  base^exp  15  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct answer  AlgEquiv  ans1  base^exp   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F       113844411  1374825739  1696156580  1388243201  611240069  1357438451  2006968171  1478302477  678440851  1219367446  1557771426   1  Test case assuming the teacher's input gets full marks.   ans1  base^exp    prt1  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt1-1-T       "
