  "title": "Simplifying Zero Index.",
  "body": " Simplifying Zero Index   Load the question by clicking the button below.       simplifying Zero index    <p>Simplify the expression below:<\/p> <p>\\[ {@coef@}{@var@}^0 \\]<\/p> <p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <h3>Worked Solution<\/h3> <p>The zero index law states that any non-zero quantity raised to the power zero equals 1.<\/p> <p>\\[ {@var@}^0 = 1. \\]<\/p> <p>So the expression becomes:<\/p> <p>\\[ {@coef@} \\times 1 = {@coef@}. \\]<\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Choose variable letter *\/ var: rand([x,y,a,b,p,q,r]); \/* Random coefficient excluding zero *\/ coef: rand_with_step(2,12,1); \/* Expression: coef * var^0 *\/ expr: coef * var^0; \/* Correct answer is just coef *\/ ans: coef; \/* Wrong answers *\/ m1: coef * 0; \/* student thinks var^0 = 0 *\/ m2: 1; \/* ignores coefficient *\/       {@ans@}    <p id=\"author\">Michael Onyimbo<\/p> <p id=\"concept\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"description\"> The question requires the learner to apply the zero index law to simplify an expression containing a variable raised to the power zero.<\/p>   1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  ans  15  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for correct answer  AlgEquiv  ans1  ans   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F       977378886  846941268  397588869  1494805824  1127091020  1458313462  1670308978  397734078  1828980173  1538962824  1318018826   1  Test case assuming the teacher's input gets full marks.   ans1  ans    prt1  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt1-1-T       "
