  "number": "1.2.40",
  "title": "Using Logarithms to Find the Power Part of Standard Form.",
  "body": " Using Logarithms to Find the Power Part of Standard Form   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Using logarithms to find the power part of standard form    <p>A scientific calculator displays a number as \\({@value2@}\\) Use logarithms to determine its standard form in the form: \\( A \\times 10^B \\) <\/p> <p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <h3>Worked Solution<\/h3> <p>We use logarithms to find the exponent B.<\/p> <p>\\[ \\log_{10}({@value2@}) = \\log_{10}({@coef2@}) + {@exp2@} \\]<\/p> <p>Thus:<\/p> <p>\\[ A = {@coef2@}, \\quad B = {@exp2@}. \\]<\/p> <p>Therefore the standard form is:<\/p> <p>\\[ {@coef2@} \\times 10^{@exp2@}. \\]<\/p>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Large number between 10^4 and 10^8 *\/ exp2: rand([4,5,6,7,8]); coef2: rand_with_step(1.2,9.8,0.2); \/* Construct value *\/ value2: coef2 * 10^exp2; \/* Standard form targets *\/ A2: coef2; B2: exp2; \/* Log components *\/ log_value: log(value2)\/log(10); \/* Wrong answers *\/ m1: log(coef2)\/log(10); \/* ignores power *\/ m2: exp2; \/* forgets coefficient *\/ m3: coef2 + exp2; \/* confusion *\/       <p>A × 10^B where 1 ≤ A &lt; 10<\/p>    <p id=\"author\">Michael Onyimbo<\/p> <p id=\"concept\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"reviewer\"><\/p> <p id=\"description\">The question requires the learner to use base-ten logarithms to identify the power of ten when converting a large number into standard form.<\/p>   1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  A2*10^B2  15  1  0   0    0  0  0  1  3     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for correct answer  AlgEquiv  ans1  A2*10^B2   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F       1132393781   1  Test case assuming the teacher's input gets full marks.   ans1  A2*10^B2    prt1  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt1-1-T       "
