  "body": " Similarity and Enlargement - Cylinders   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Similarity and Enlargement Cylinders _Surface Area, Length, and Volume Relationships (copy)    <p><strong>Two cylinders, P and Q, are mathematically similar.<\/strong><\/p> [[jsxgraph]] var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard('jxgbox', { boundingbox: [-60, -60, 90, 90], axis: false, visible: false, showCopyright: false, showNavigation: true, keepAspectRatio: true }); \/* Cylinder P *\/ var radiusP = 10; var heightP = 60; \/\/ Bottom ellipse (P) board.create('ellipse', [ [-25, 0], [-25 + radiusP, 0], [-25, 3] ], {strokeColor: '#000', fillColor: '#ccc', fillOpacity: 0.3, fixed: true}); \/\/ Top ellipse (P) board.create('ellipse', [ [-25, heightP], [-25 + radiusP, heightP], [-25, heightP + 3] ], {strokeColor: '#000', fillColor: '#ccc', fillOpacity: 0.3, fixed: true}); \/\/ Side lines (P) board.create('segment', [[-26.7, 0], [-26.7, heightP]], {strokeColor: '#000', fixed: true}); board.create('segment', [[-13.5, 0], [-13.5, heightP]], {strokeColor: '#000', fixed: true}); \/\/ Labels (P) board.create('text', [-25 + radiusP + 3, heightP \/ 2, 'Length = {#L_P#} cm'], {fixed: true}); board.create('text', [-20, heightP + 5, '<b>Cylinder P<\/b>'], {fixed: true}); \/* Cylinder Q *\/ var radiusQ = 15; var heightQ = 80; \/\/ Bottom ellipse (Q) board.create('ellipse', [ [20, 0], [20 + radiusQ, 0], [20, 3] ], {strokeColor: '#000', fillColor: '#cde', fillOpacity: 0.3, fixed: true}); \/\/ Top ellipse (Q) board.create('ellipse', [ [20, heightQ], [20 + radiusQ, heightQ], [20, heightQ + 3] ], {strokeColor: '#000', fillColor: '#cde', fillOpacity: 0.3, fixed: true}); \/\/ Side lines (Q) board.create('segment', [[18.3, 0], [18.3, heightQ]], {strokeColor: '#000', fixed: true}); board.create('segment', [[35, 0], [35, heightQ]], {strokeColor: '#000', fixed: true}); \/\/ Labels (Q) board.create('text', [20 + radiusQ + 3, heightQ \/ 2, 'Length = ?'], {fixed: true}); board.create('text', [25, heightQ + 5, '<b>Cylinder Q<\/b>'], {fixed: true}); [[\/jsxgraph]] <hr> <ul> <li>Total surface area of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> = {@ SA_P @} cm²<\/li> <li>Total surface area of cylinder <strong>Q<\/strong> = {@ SA_Q @} cm²<\/li> <li>Length of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> = {@ L_P @} cm<\/li> <\/ul> <p><strong>(a)<\/strong> Work out the length of cylinder Q.<\/p> <p>Give your answer in cm.<\/p> <p>Length of cylinder Q = [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]<\/p> <hr> <p>The volume of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> is {@ V_P @} cm³.<\/p> <p><strong>(b)<\/strong> Work out the volume of cylinder Q.<\/p> <p>Give your answer in cm³.<\/p> <p>Volume of cylinder Q = [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]<\/p> <hr> <details> <summary><strong>Hints (click to expand)<\/strong><\/summary> <ul> <li>For similar solids: area scale factor = (length scale factor)²<\/li> <li>Volume scale factor = (length scale factor)³<\/li> <li>Length scale factor = √(area scale factor)<\/li> <\/ul> <\/details>    <h5><strong>Worked Solution<\/strong><\/h5> <p><strong>Lets first look at what we are given:<\/strong><\/p> <ul> <li>Total surface area of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> = {@ SA_P @} cm²<\/li> <li>Total surface area of cylinder <strong>Q<\/strong> = {@ SA_Q @} cm²<\/li> <li>Length of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> = {@ L_P @} cm<\/li> <li>Volume of cylinder <strong>P<\/strong> = {@ V_P @} cm³<\/li> <\/ul> <h5><strong>(a)<\/strong> Find the length of cylinder Q<\/h5> <ol> <li>Find the area (surface area) scale factor:<br> \\( \\text{Area scale factor} = \\dfrac{S_Q}{S_P} = \\dfrac{{@ SA_Q @}}{{@ SA_P @}} = {@ scale_factor_area @} \\)<\/li><br> <li>Find the linear (length) scale factor:<br> Since area scale factor = (length scale factor)²,<br> \\( \\text{Length scale factor} = \\sqrt{{@ scale_factor_area @}} = {@ scale_factor_length @} \\)<\/li><br> <li>Find the length of Q:<br> \\( L_Q = {@ L_P @} \\times {@ scale_factor_length @} = {@ L_Q @}\\ \\text{cm} \\)<\/li> <\/ol> <p><strong>Answer (a):<\/strong> {@ ta_ans1 @} cm<\/p> <hr> <h5><strong>(b)<\/strong> Find the volume of cylinder Q<\/h5> <ol> <li>Find the volume scale factor:<br> \\( \\text{Volume scale factor} = (\\text{length scale factor})^3 = {@ scale_factor_length @}^3 = {@ scale_factor_volume @} \\)<\/li><br> <li>Find the volume of Q:<br> \\( V_Q = {@ V_P @} \\times {@ scale_factor_volume @} = {@ V_Q @}\\ \\text{cm}^3 \\)<\/li> <\/ol> <p><strong>Answer (b):<\/strong> {@ ta_ans2 @} cm³<\/p> <hr> <p><em>Summary:<\/em><\/p> <ul> <li><strong>Length of cylinder Q:<\/strong> {@ ta_ans1 @} cm<\/li> <li><strong>Volume of cylinder Q:<\/strong> {@ ta_ans2 @} cm³<\/li> <\/ul>   1  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Randomised variables *\/ \/* Surface areas*\/ SA_P : 10*rand_with_step(5,12,1); \/* total surface area of cylinder P (e.g. 50–120 cm²) *\/ scale_factor_area : rand([4,9,16,25]); \/* area scale factor between 4 and 25 *\/ SA_Q : SA_P * scale_factor_area; \/* Linear scale factor *\/ scale_factor_length : sqrt(scale_factor_area); \/* Lengths *\/ L_P : rand_with_step(3,6,1); \/* length of cylinder P (3–6 cm) *\/ L_Q : L_P * scale_factor_length; \/* Volumes *\/ V_P : 10*rand_with_step(8,15,1); \/*volume of cylinder P (80–150 cm³) *\/ scale_factor_volume : scale_factor_length^3; V_Q : V_P * scale_factor_volume; \/* Answers *\/ ta_ans1 : decimalplaces(L_Q,2); \/* length of Q *\/ ta_ans2 : decimalplaces(V_Q,2); \/* volume of Q *\/       <br>{@ta_ans1 @} <br>{@ta_ans2 @}      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  ta_ans1  8  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  1     ans2  algebraic  ta_ans2  8  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  1     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0   AlgEquiv  ans1  ta_ans1   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F        prt2  1.0000000  1  1      0   AlgEquiv  ans2  ta_ans2   0  =  1   -1  prt2-1-T     =  0   -1  prt2-1-F          "
