  "title": "Finding Trigonometric Ratios in a Right Angled Triangle (45°).",
  "body": " Finding Trigonometric Ratios in a Right Angled Triangle (45°)   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Finding Trigonometric Ratios in a Right-Angled Triangle    <p>Look at the figure below and use it to find the following trigonometric ratios:<\/p> [[jsxgraph]] var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, { boundingbox: [-1, 4.5, 6, -1], axis: false, showNavigation: false, showCopyright: false }); \/\/ Points with labels only (no circles) var Q = board.create('point', [0, 0], { name: 'Q', fixed: true, visible: false, label: {offset: [-15, -10], visible: true} }); var R = board.create('point', [4, 0], { name: 'R', fixed: true, visible: false, label: {offset: [10, -10], visible: true} }); var P = board.create('point', [0, 3], { name: 'P', fixed: true, visible: false, label: {offset: [-15, 10], visible: true} }); \/\/ Triangle sides board.create('segment', [Q, R]); board.create('segment', [Q, P]); board.create('segment', [P, R]); \/\/ Right-angle at Q board.create('angle', [P, Q, R], { radius: 0.4, type: 'square', name: '' }); \/\/ Angle θ at R (inside) board.create('angle', [P, R, Q], { radius: 0.6, name: '45°' }); \/\/ Length labels board.create('text', [-0.6, 1.5, '{#side#} cm']); board.create('text', [2, -0.4, '{#side#} cm']); [[\/jsxgraph]] <ol type='i'> <li>\\(\\text{Length of side PR }=\\)[[input:ans1]]\\(\\,\\text{cm}\\)[[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]<\/li> <li>\\(Tan \\,45^\\circ=\\)[[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]<\/li> <li>\\(Cos\\,45^\\circ=\\)[[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]]<\/li> <li>\\(Sin\\,45^\\circ=\\)[[input:ans4]][[validation:ans4]][[feedback:prt4]]<\/li> <\/ol> <p><\/p>    <p><strong>Worked Solution:<\/strong><\/p> <p>Given a right-angled triangle PQR with right angle at Q and angle \\( \\angle R = 45^\\circ \\). Let the sides opposite and adjacent to the 45° angle be equal to <em>side<\/em> cm.<\/p> <ol type='i'> <li> <p>Length of side PR (hypotenuse):<\/p> <p> Using Pythagoras theorem: <br> \\(\\begin{align} PR &= \\sqrt{PQ^2 + QR^2} \\\\ &= \\sqrt{{@side@}^2 + {@side@}^2} \\\\ &= \\sqrt{2 \\cdot {@side@}^2} \\\\ &= {@RP@}\\, \\text{ cm} \\end{align}\\) <\/p> <\/li> <li> <p>\\(Tan \\,45^\\circ\\):<\/p> <p> \\(\\begin{align} \\tan 45^\\circ &= \\frac{\\text{Opposite}}{\\text{Adjacent}} \\\\ &= \\frac{PQ}{QR} \\\\ &= \\frac{{@side@}}{{@side@}}\\\\ &= {@tan_45@} \\end{align}\\) <\/p> <\/li> <li> <p>\\(Cos\\,45^\\circ\\):<\/p> <p> \\(\\begin{align} \\cos 45^\\circ &= \\frac{\\text{Adjacent}}{\\text{Hypotenuse}} \\\\ &= \\frac{{@side@}}{{@RP@}} \\\\ &= {@cos_45@} &\\approx 0.707 \\end{align}\\) <\/p> <\/li> <li> <p>\\(Sin\\,45^\\circ\\):<\/p> <p> \\(\\begin{align} \\sin 45^\\circ &= \\frac{\\text{Opposite}}{\\text{Hypotenuse}} \\\\ &= \\frac{{@side@}}{{@RP@}}\\\\ &={@sin_45@}\\\\ & \\approx 0.707 \\end{align}\\) <\/p> <\/li> <\/ol>   15  0.1  0    2025073100    Angle:45; \/*The special angle 45*\/ side:rand_with_step(1,26,4);\/*Randomizing the side of the triangle that is opposite and adjasment*\/ RP:sqrt(side^2+side^2); \/*Finding the Hypotenues of the triangle*\/ \/*Solution of the trigonometric ratios of angle 45 degrees.*\/ tan_45:side\/side; cos_45:side\/RP; sin_45:side\/RP;       <p>\\(\\text{The angle given}={@Angle@}^\\circ\\)<p> <p>\\(\\text{Length PR}={@RP@}\\,\\text{cm}\\)<p> <p>\\(Tan\\,45^\\circ={@tan_45@}\\)<p> <p>\\(Cos\\,45^\\circ={@cos_45@}\\)<p> <p>\\(Sin\\,45^\\circ={@sin_45@}\\)<p>      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  RP  7  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     ans2  algebraic  tan_45  7  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     ans3  algebraic  cos_45  7  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     ans4  algebraic  sin_45  7  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct length  AlgEquiv  ans1  RP   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F        prt2  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct angle.  AlgEquiv  ans2  tan_45   0  =  1   -1  prt2-1-T     =  0   -1  prt2-1-F        prt3  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct cosine  AlgEquiv  ans3  cos_45   0  =  1   -1  prt3-1-T     =  0   -1  prt3-1-F        prt4  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct sine.  AlgEquiv  ans4  sin_45   0  =  1   -1  prt4-1-T     =  0   -1  prt4-1-F       707128844  192637798  32843412  51332121  748836221  1150621624   1  Test case assuming the teacher's input gets full marks.   ans1  RP    ans2  tan_45    ans3  cos_45    ans4  sin_45    prt1  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt1-1-T    prt2  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt2-1-T    prt3  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt3-1-T    prt4  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt4-1-T       "
