  "title": "Determining the Length of a Divider Arm from Vertical Height.",
  "body": " Determining the Length of a Divider Arm from Vertical Height   Load the question by clicking the button below.       Determining the Length of a Divider Arm from Vertical Height    <p>The angle formed by the arms of an upright pair of dividers and the horizontal is \\({@theta@}^\\circ\\). The vertical distance from the horizontal to the vertex is \\({@d@}\\,\\text{cm}\\). Find the length of one arm of the divider without using a calculator or trigonometric tables.<\/p> <p>\\(\\text{The Length of a divider arm from vertical height}=\\)[[input:ans1]]\\(\\,\\text{cm}\\)[[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]<\/p>    <p><strong>Worked Solution:<\/strong><\/p> <p>We are asked to find the length of one arm of the divider given:<\/p> <ul> <li>Angle with horizontal: {@theta@}°<\/li> <li>Vertical distance from horizontal to vertex: \\({@d@}\\, \\text{cm}\\)<\/li> <\/ul> <p>From trigonometry, for an upright divider forming an angle \\(\\theta\\) with the horizontal, the relationship between the vertical height and the arm length is:<\/p> <p> \\(\\begin{align} \\text{Arm length} &= \\frac{\\text{Vertical distance}}{\\sin \\theta} \\\\ &= \\frac{@d@}{\\sin({@theta@}^\\circ)} \\\\ &= {@arm_length@} \\text{ cm} \\end{align}\\) <\/p> <p>Hence, the length of one arm of the divider is {@arm_length@} cm.<\/p>   15  0.1  0    2025073100    \/* Randomize the vertical distance from 5 to 25 cm in steps of 1 *\/ d: rand_with_step(1,56,4); \/* Angle of 45 degrees *\/ theta: 45; \/* Convert degrees to radians for computation *\/ theta_rad: theta * %pi\/180; \/* Length of one arm of the divider *\/ arm_length: d \/ sin(theta_rad);       <p>\\(\\text{The angle made by the pair of divider is} ={@theta@}^\\circ\\)<\/p> <p>\\(\\text{The distance}={@d@}\\,\\text{cm}\\)<\/p> <p>\\(\\text{The Length of a divider arm from vertical height}={@arm_length@}\\,\\text{cm}\\)<\/p>      1  0  0   <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:green;\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"><\/i><\/span> Correct answer, well done.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:orange;\"><i class=\"fa fa-adjust\"><\/i><\/span> Your answer is partially correct.    <span style=\"font-size: 1.5em; color:red;\"><i class=\"fa fa-times\"><\/i><\/span> Incorrect answer.   .  *10  none  1  i  cos-1  lang  [  0    ans1  algebraic  arm_length  7  1  0   0    1  0  0  1  3     prt1  1.0000000  1  1      0  Checks for the correct Length.  AlgEquiv  ans1  arm_length   0  =  1   -1  prt1-1-T     =  0   -1  prt1-1-F       463734286  1283760297  13384997  663029925  2100032474  1598453226  1703353731  1427792288  2098633323   1  Test case assuming the teacher's input gets full marks.   ans1  arm_length    prt1  1.0000000  0.0000000  prt1-1-T       "
